articipate in it and all the participants won many gifts and they were happy a lot. Moreover, Ocean Supercenter’s Family Week made the families fun with stilt walkers, face-painting program, and many others fun activities. In the entertainmentprogram, Bunny Phyoe and Athen Cho Swe perform and sing their songs at North Point Shopping Center and Nyan Lynn Aung and Yadana Mai at Ocean Supercenter (Pazundaung).\r\nOcean Supercenter organized the whole event with Premier Coffee and Herballines  as main sponsors and co sponsors are Anlene, Biogesic, Champs, CP, Dentiste’, E-Lan, Top Cashew Brittle and Yum Yum.\r\n \r\n','Ocean Family Week','City Mart would like invite to our Kids because Santa Claus will visit to City Mart for gift distribution on 23rd, 24th &amp; 25th from 5 pm to 7 pm.','inherit','open','open','','124-revision-4','','','2012-12-28 03:03:55','2012-12-28 03:03:55','',124,'http://oceansupercenter.com.mm/uncategorized/124-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(196,1,'2012-12-28 03:04:35','2012-12-28 03:04:35','With the slogan “Best Value Best Products and More”, Ocean Supercenter is always trying to offer best products to their customers whenshopping. The traditional food fair was held from the date of 2012 November 27 to 2 December at all Ocean Supercenters.  In this sales promotion, Ocean Supercenter provided and organized a lot of traditional foods from many areas of the whole country such as Shan (North / South), Mandalay, A Nyar (middle Myanmar), Pyin Oo Lwin and Ayarwady. They created this event with traditional theme and so they built many bamboo tents and sell the traditional foods with the staff who wore traditional costume.Moreover, customers could vote their favourite tents and the voters can winlucky draw Ocean Supercenter gift vouchers worth Ks 30,000. The customers enjoyed the event and this program is one of the ways to promote Myanmar Traditional Foods.','Traditional Food Fair','City Mart Supermarket ( Thamin e  )  presented  Live DJ Weekends (Second part) which is the most popularities in Customer on weekends.','inherit','open','open','','122-revision-4','','','2012-12-28 03:04:35','2012-12-28 03:04:35','',122,'http://oceansupercenter.com.mm/uncategorized/122-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(197,1,'2012-12-28 03:05:28','2012-12-28 03:05:28','With the slogan “Best Value Best Products and More”, Ocean Supercenter is always trying to entertain their customers when shopping. Beauty Fair was held from the date of 2012 October 20 to 31 at all Ocean Supercenter.  In this sales promotion, Ocean Supercenter provided and organized many cosmetics and beauty accessories with special discount. In the sales promotion program, the fifty years old and above customers got 50% discount from Revlon and L’Oreal’s selected products.\r\nWith the sales promotion, they organized a Mrs. Ocean BeautyPageant competition. There were many contestants in this competition. In October 28 at North Point Shopping Center, they chose eight contestants for the final competition and in October 20 at Ocean Supercenter (Pazundaung), theychose Mrs. Ocean Beauty Pageant, 1st Runner Up and 2nd Runner Up. Moreover, Ocean Supercenter held the donation program at School & Training for Girls (Yangon) with the winners in November 17.  In this donation program, the famous author Nu Nu Yee (Innwa) joined and motivated the girls with the title “Poem & Child”. The girls enjoyed the speech and Ocean Supercenter donated some necessary things for them.\r\nOcean Supercenter organized the whole event with Bio-essence, bsc cosmetology, FOLLOW ME, GINVERA, Kanebo, L’OREAL, NIVEA and REVLON.','Mrs. Ocean Beauty Pageant & Beauty Fair','City Mart was  organized  “2013 Stylish New Range ” &amp; product launch on December 09, 2012 at marketplace by City Mart. ','inherit','open','open','','119-revision-5','','','2012-12-28 03:05:28','2012-12-28 03:05:28','',119,'http://oceansupercenter.com.mm/uncategorized/119-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(665,1,'2013-05-03 08:57:11',