ulation through outlet expansions and the introduction of new retail concepts. While increasing our footprint, we take into account the impact that our actions have on our employees, customers, society, and the environment.</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>For more information, please contact: <br /> EaindraPhay, PR Department, City Mart Holdings Co., Ltd. <br /> email: </em></strong><strong><em>enquiry@city.com.mm    mobile:959 73031507<br /> tel: 951 508460 - 6 / fax: 951 512019</em></strong><em></em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Special Mother’s Day Promotion','To celebrate this coming Mother’s Day, Ocean Supercenter will feature more than 100 items suitable for mothers’ needs from healthy foods to clothings to beauty care in our special Mother’s Day Promotion from the 26th April – 12th May 2013.','inherit','open','open','','650-revision-2','','','2013-04-25 09:00:59','2013-04-25 09:00:59','',650,'http://oceansupercenter.com.mm/uncategorized/650-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(664,1,'2013-02-26 07:37:55','2013-02-26 07:37:55','<p><strong>Fruit, Vegetable, Chilled Processed Food, Chilled Ready Made Food, Fresh Meat and Seafood.</strong></p>\r\n<p>We offer fresh food products like fruit, vegetables, fresh meat etc, to our customers everyday. We are very careful about our food freshness to ensure the highest levels of quality for all of our shoppers. We proudly support our local suppliers so we not only stock the best imported foods but the best local produce as well.</p>\r\n','Fresh Food','We offer fresh food products like fruits, vegetables, fresh meat, etc. to the customers. We take care of our food freshness to safe for the consumers. Not only the local fresh foods but also the imported fresh foods are available.','inherit','open','open','','23-revision-13','','','2013-02-26 07:37:55','2013-02-26 07:37:55','',23,'http://oceansupercenter.com.mm/uncategorized/23-revision-13/',0,'revision','',0),(347,1,'2013-01-10 04:16:06','2013-01-10 04:16:06','<a href=\"http://oceansupercenter.com.mm/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/1355283280imgdetails13.png\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-331\" title=\"1355283280imgdetails1\" src=\"http://oceansupercenter.com.mm/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/1355283280imgdetails13.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"582\" height=\"284\" /></a>\r\n\r\nWith the slogan “Best Value Best Products and More”, Ocean Supercenter is always trying to entertain their customers when shopping. Ocean Family Week was held from the date of 2012 December 5 to 9 at the North Point Shopping Center and the promotion areas of Ocean Supercenter (Pazundaung). In this sales promotion, Ocean Supercenter featured food, Fashion (Men, Women, Kids), Toys, Home Appliances, Electronic Products, Furniture, Kitchen Ware and other popular household items for families.\r\n\r\nDuring the sales promotion program, customers had the chance to win the lucky draw “Gold Prizes” complete with the logo of Ocean Supercenter. On the final day of the sales promotion, the lucky draw winners were selected. They created this event with carnival theme that captured the feeling of a Myanmar bazaar. To make the customers’ children even happier, Ocean Supercenter arranged for a small amusement zone organized by Happy World.\r\n\r\nThere were two entertainment programs on 8-Dec-2012 at Ocean Supercenter (North Point Branch) and 9-Dec-2012 at Ocean Supercenter (Pazundaung). The customers enjoyed a magic show, a dance performance by models, a product and fashion show but, especially, the game program organized by Dream Boat Entertainment. In the game program, a huge number of customers participated. All the participants were ecstatic as there were many gift give-aways making the occasion even more special. Taking fun to new heights, Ocean Supercenter’s Family Week featured stilt walkers, face-painting and many other fun activities. In the entertainment program, Bunny Phyoe and Athen Cho Swe performed and song their pop songs at North Point Shopping Center and Nyan Lynn Aung and Yadana Mai at Ocean Supercenter (Pazundaung). Ocean Supercenter organized the whole event with Premier Coffee and Herballines as the main sponsors. Co-sponsors were Anlene, Biogesic, Champs, CP, Dentiste’, E-Lan, Top Cashew Brittle and Yum Yum.','Ocean Family Week','City Mart would like invite to our Kids because Santa Claus will visit to City Mart for gift distribution on 23rd, 24th &amp; 25th from 5 pm to 7 pm.','inherit','open','open','','124-revision-10','','','2013-01-10 04:16:06','2013-01-10 04:16:06','',124,'http://oceansupercenter.com.mm/uncategorized/124-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),(355,1,'2013-01-15 04:08:17','2013-01-15 04:08:17','','20121208_142953','','inherit','open','open','','20121208_142953','','','2013-01-15 04:08:17','2013-01-15 04:08:17','',124,'http://oceansupercenter.com.mm/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/20121208_142953.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(348,1,'2013-01-07 04:28:25','2013-01-07 04:28:25','<p>With the slogan “Best Value Best Products and More”, Ocean Supercenter is always offering their best products to customers when shopping. The traditional food fair was held from the date of 2012 November 27 to 2 December at all Ocean Supercenters.  During this time, Ocean Supercenter provided and featured many of the delicious traditional foods from provinces all over the country such as Shan (North / South), Mandalay, A Nyar (middle Myanmar), Pyin Oo Lwin and Ayarwady. They created this event with a traditional theme so there were many bamboo tents constructed inside which you could sample tasty traditional food and see staff resplendent in traditional costumes. Customers then voted for their favourite tents and were automatically entered into a lucky draw. The prize was Ocean Supercenter gift vouchers worth Ks 30,000. The customers enjoyed the event and Ocean Supercentre found this is a very effective way to promote Traditional Food of Myanmar.</p>','Traditional Food Fair','City Mart Supermarket ( Thamin e  )  presented  Live DJ Weekends (Secon